Uses of Package
com.k2.Proforma

  • Classes in com.k2.Proforma used by com.k2.Proforma 
    Class and Description
    AbstractPart
    The abstract part provides the conditional part handling for parameter and string parts
    Line
    This class represents a line of proforma parts
    Parameter
    This class represents a parameterized String value The value of the parameter can be set to a literal string value or can be set to the value returned from a CallBack of type string.
    ParameterPart
    This class represents a parameterized part of a proforma line
    Part
    This interface defines parts of a proforma line
    Proforma
    A proforma is a simple string template comprising lines of parts Each line in the proforma is output to the given writer with a implementation system specific carriage return or the carriage return specified by the call to setCarriageReturn(...) Each line comprises parts.
    Proforma.CarriageReturn
    A convenience enumeration to specify the MS DOS carriage return or the UNIX carriage return
    ProformaOutput
    The proforma output is an implementation of the ParamterEvaluator interface and as such can provide values for the parameters in a proforma.
    StringPart
    This class represents a static string on a proforma line
